text: A late-night newscast (or late local news) is a television newscast on many American networks at 11:00 p.m. Eastern Time nightly. All other time zones air their last newscasts of the day at 10:00 p.m. local time. FOX affiliates have a 10:00 p.m. newscast. The news precedes primetime and before late-night television. Category:American television news programs
title: Late-night newscast
